      Modifier and Type Method Description
      CodeRepresentation UmlCodeConverter.convertUmlToCodeRepresentation​(UmlModel umlModel, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> qualifiedNames, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> associationTypes)

    • Uses of CodeRepresentation in umlcode.converter.element

      Methods in umlcode.converter.element with parameters of type CodeRepresentation 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      static void FieldConverter.applyCollectionTypes​(CodeRepresentation codeRepresentation, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> collectionTypes)
      Replaces the type attribute of all CodeFields of the given CodeRepresentation with a potential matching collection type of the given MapDB database.
      static void ElementConverter.convertElements​(UmlModel umlModel, CodeRepresentation codeRepresentation, TemporaryModel tmpModel)
      Static method converting the UmlElements of a given UmlModel to CodeElements for the CodeRepresentation.
      If the UmlModel contains UmlElements at the top level, a CodePackage is created, where the converted CodeElements are added to.
      static CodePackage PackageConverter.createTopLevelPackage​(CodeRepresentation codeRepresentation)
      Creates a CodePackage with the name of the given CodeRepresentation.
      This function is called, if the UmlModel to be converted contains UmlElements as direct child elements.
      In this case, the converted CodeElement are grouped in the returned CodePackage.
      All sub CodePackages of the CodeRepresentation which names start with the name of the representation are added to the newly created CodePackage because with the representation name as prefix, they are considered subpackages.
      CodePackages without this prefix in their name are considered external packages and are kept as child packages of the CodeRepresentation object.
      static void QualifiedNamesConverter.resolveQualifiedNames​(CodeRepresentation codeRepresentation, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> qualifiedNamesDB)
      Sets qualified names for all CodeElements of the given CodeRepresentation and replaces the type attributes of CodeParameters and CodeTemplateParameters with potential qualified names, if their type is one of the CodeElements.
